# Glass & Floating UI

Follow the floating back button in `property-panel.tsx` and tokens in `@/lib/utils`.

## Glass surfaces

Reuse shared constants — never hand-roll glass classes:

```tsx
import { cn, GLASS_SURFACE, GLASS_PANEL } from "@/lib/utils"

// ✅ Card sections
<Card className={cn(GLASS_SURFACE, "gap-0 overflow-hidden py-0")} />
// ✅ Plain bordered panels
<div className={cn("rounded-lg p-4", GLASS_PANEL)} />
// ❌ One-off glass strings
<div className="bg-[var(--bg-2)]/80 backdrop-blur-sm shadow-..." />
```

Use tokens: `var(--ink)`, `var(--bg)`, `var(--bg-2)`, `var(--line)`, `var(--line-2)`.

## Floating sticky controls

Float the control, not a full-width bar:

```tsx
// ✅ w-fit wrapper; glass on the button only
<div className="sticky top-0 z-10 w-fit">
  <Button variant="outline" className="border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--bg)]/80 backdrop-blur-sm shadow-[0_2px_8px_-2px_rgba(0,0,0,0.12)] ..." />
</div>
// ❌ Full-width opaque strip
<div className="sticky top-0 border-b bg-background shadow-md"><Button /></div>
```

## Layout & UX

- **Segmented views**: Cards/sections (header, at-a-glance, upcoming, quick links) — not one bloated scroll.
- **Lean detail views**: no admin/settings duplication on user-facing panels.
- **shadcn first**: compose `@/components/ui/*`; install via CLI when missing.
- **i18n**: `COPY: Record<Locale, CopyShape>` for user-facing strings.
- **lazy-shadcn**: minimum code; match existing pixels.
